Increased economic growth: With access to high-quality education, individuals would have the skills and knowledge necessary to contribute more effectively to the workforce, leading to increased productivity and economic growth.
Reduced poverty: Education is a key factor in breaking the cycle of poverty, as it can lead to higher-paying jobs and greater financial stability.

Improved health outcomes: Education has been shown to be associated with better health outcomes, as individuals with higher levels of education are more likely to make informed decisions about their health and seek preventive care.
Enhanced social mobility: Access to high-quality education can provide individuals with the opportunity to move up the social ladder and improve their status in society.

Increased of: With access to high-quality education, individuals would have a better understanding of their of the laws and regulations that govern society, leading to a more informed and engaged citizenry.
